 :tx/rationale "RISK: Phase 1 (DAEMON-WRITE) may INCREASE write latency in worst case. Currently each agent loads its own Store (~300ms) and writes immediately. With daemon routing, the agent sends over socket and WAITS for the daemon. If the daemon is busy processing a 3s status request for another agent, the write queues behind it. Worst case: 3s write latency (from 300ms). This is because the daemon is single-threaded (Phase 1 doesn't add multi-threading — that's Phase 2). MITIGATION ALREADY IN DW3: The daemon routing has a 10s read timeout (daemon.rs:839). But this is too long. DW3 should set a 2s timeout for write commands specifically. If the daemon doesn't respond in 2s, fall back to direct mode. This ensures writes never exceed max(2s_timeout + direct_mode_load, daemon_response). With DW0+DW0b, direct mode is correct (self-correcting staleness). The timeout fallback is safe. ACTION: Update DW3 description to include write-specific timeout of 2s with direct-mode fallback."
